As a Korean-American.....I am in awe of this Moroccan team. They have played tremendous futbol in this cup. Their defense and goalkeeping has been exquisite. And just the speed and precision of their counter attack is a sight to behold. They know who they are and they stay disciplined to executing their style of play.  They are happy to let opposing teams dominate possession but clamp down on scoring opportunities...and as soon as the other team makes a mistake they are off to the races and efficient in making the most of their counter attacks. Just a beautiful and solid TEAM...I will be rooting on the Atlas Lions as they face another big test in France. Congratulations Morocco...you have represented your nation with honor...given the entire continent of Africa a sense of pride...and shown on the World stage that you belong amongst the greats.

Bad Portugal strategy. They had some shots and headers with potential but played too slow like they have for 12+ years. Too much lateral passing waiting for an opening. When they went up midfielders would all hang on the edge of the box and with no opening would just pass over to the wing to pray for a good cross. It’s hard to sit back waiting for the opening when a team defends with 9 or 10 in the box. That’s why Ramos barely touched the ball and Ronaldo had more involvement when he was playing for Guerrero than when he moved into the middle after Ramos came off. The few time Morroco countered and failed, when Portugal needed a fast counter they’d stop the ball in midfield and pass around letting all the Moroccans drop back. Needed to make more of their chances on the counter instead of sitting back  and resorting to crosses once they realized there was no opening. It wouldn’t work but they didn’t adapt.

Notice: A person from Morocco is called Moor.

"The Portuguese shield is one of the oldest elements of the country’s flag, with a similar shield appearing during the reign of Sancho I. The shield was only not present on a flag during the reign of Afonso I.

The shield is divided into an interior white section with 5 smaller blue shields, and an outer red area with 7 yellow castles.

The 7 yellow castles on the red part represent the 7 castles that Portugal took back from the Moors during battles. These were captured under Afonso III in the Algarve in 1249. 

The 5 smaller blue shields in the white area of the shield represent the 5 Moorish [Muslims] kings that were killed by Afonso I, the first King of Portugal. There are also 5 white dots within each blue shield representing the 5 wounds of Christ, the five wounds Christ suffered during the crucifixion."
